{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id529d8919-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1295"},"text":"§ 1295.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Jurisdiction of the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id529d891a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit shall have exclusive jurisdiction—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d891b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal from a final decision of a district court of the United States, the District Court of Guam, the District Court of the Virgin Islands, or the District Court of the Northern Mariana Islands, in any civil action arising under, or in any civil action in which a party has asserted a compulsory counterclaim arising under, any Act of Congress relating to patents or plant variety protection;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d891c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal from a final decision of a district court of the United States, the United States District Court for the District of the Canal Zone, the District Court of Guam, the District Court of the Virgin Islands, or the District Court for the Northern Mariana Islands, if the jurisdiction of that court was based, in whole or in part, on ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1346"},"text":"section 1346 of this title","children":[],"tail":", except that jurisdiction of an appeal in a case brought in a district court under section 1346(a)(1), 1346(b), 1346(e), or 1346(f) of this title or under section 1346(a)(2) when the claim is founded upon an Act of Congress or a regulation of an executive department providing for internal revenue shall be governed by sections 1291, 1292, and 1294 of this title;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d891d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal from a final decision of the United States Court of Federal Claims;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d891e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal from a decision of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d891f-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/4/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Patent Trial and Appeal Board of the United States Patent and Trademark Office with respect to a patent application, derivation proceeding, reexamination, post-grant review, or inter partes review under title 35, at the instance of a party who exercised that party’s right to participate in the applicable proceeding before or appeal to the Board, except that an applicant or a party to a derivation proceeding may also have remedy by civil action pursuant to section 145 or 146 of title 35; an appeal under this subparagraph of a decision of the Board with respect to an application or derivation proceeding shall waive the right of such applicant or party to proceed under section 145 or 146 of title 35;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8920-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/4/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Under Secretary of Commerce for Intellectual Property and Director of the United States Patent and Trademark Office or the Trademark Trial and Appeal Board with respect to applications for registration of marks and other proceedings as provided in section 21 of the Trademark Act of 1946 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1071"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 1071","children":[],"tail":"); or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8921-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/4/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a district court to which a case was directed pursuant to section 145, 146, or 154(b) of title 35;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8922-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal from a final decision of the United States Court of International Trade;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8923-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to review the final determinations of the United States International Trade Commission relating to unfair practices in import trade, made under section 337 of the Tariff Act of 1930 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1337"},"text":"19 U.S.C. 1337","children":[],"tail":");"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8924-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to review, by appeal on questions of law only, findings of the Secretary of Commerce under U.S. note 6 to subchapter X of chapter 98 of the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States (relating to importation of instruments or apparatus);","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8925-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal under section 71 of the Plant Variety Protection Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s2461"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 2461","children":[],"tail":");"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8926-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal from a final order or final decision of the Merit Systems Protection Board, pursuant to sections 7703(b)(1) and 7703(d) of title 5;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8927-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"(10)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal from a final decision of an agency board of contract appeals pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s7107/a/1"},"text":"section 7107(a)(1) of title 41","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8928-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/11"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11"},"text":"(11)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal under section 211 of the Economic Stabilization Act of 1970;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d8929-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/12"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12"},"text":"(12)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal under section 5 of the Emergency Petroleum Allocation Act of 1973;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d892a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/13"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"13"},"text":"(13)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal under section 506(c) of the Natural Gas Policy Act of 1978; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id529d892b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/a/14"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"14"},"text":"(14)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" of an appeal under section 523 of the Energy Policy and Conservation Act.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id529d892c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The head of any executive department or agency may, with the approval of the Attorney General, refer to the Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit for judicial review any final decision rendered by a board of contract appeals pursuant to the terms of any contract with the United States awarded by that department or agency which the head of such department or agency has concluded is not entitled to finality pursuant to the review standards specified in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s7107/b"},"text":"section 7107(b) of title 41","children":[],"tail":". The head of each executive department or agency shall make any referral under this section within one hundred and twenty days after the receipt of a copy of the final appeal decision."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id529d892d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1295/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit shall review the matter referred in accordance with the standards specified in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s7107/b"},"text":"section 7107(b) of title 41","children":[],"tail":". The court shall proceed with judicial review on the administrative record made before the board of contract appeals on matters so referred as in other cases pending in such court, shall determine the issue of finality of the appeal decision, and shall, if appropriate, render judgment thereon, or remand the matter to any administrative or executive body or official with such direction as it may deem proper and just."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id529d892e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/164/tI/s127/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–164, title I, § 127(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-04-02"},"text":"Apr. 2, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/37"},"text":"96 Stat. 37","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/622/tII/s205/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–622, title II, § 205(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-11-08"},"text":"Nov. 8, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/3388"},"text":"98 Stat. 3388","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418/tI/s1214/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418, title I, § 1214(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-08-23"},"text":"Aug. 23, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/1156"},"text":"102 Stat. 1156","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/702/tX/s1020/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–702, title X, § 1020(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-19"},"text":"Nov. 19, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/4671"},"text":"102 Stat. 4671","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/572/tI/s102/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–572, title I, § 102(c)","children":[],"tail":", title IX, § 902(b)(1), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-29"},"text":"Oct. 29, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4507"},"text":"106 Stat. 4507","children":[],"tail":", 4516; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4402/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, §§ 4402(b)(2), 4732(b)(14)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–560, 1501A–584; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s5/g/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 5(g)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-01-04"},"text":"Jan. 4, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/3848"},"text":"124 Stat. 3848","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":", §§ 7(c)(2), 19(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/314"},"text":"125 Stat. 314","children":[],"tail":", 331.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id529d892f-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id529d8930-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id529d8931-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States, referred to in subsec. (a)(7), is not set out in the Code. See Publication of Harmonized Tariff Schedule note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1202"},"text":"section 1202 of Title 19","children":[],"tail":", Customs Duties."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 211 of the Economic Stabilization Act of 1970, referred to in subsec. (a)(11), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/379/s211"},"text":"section 211 of Pub. L. 91–379","children":[],"tail":", title II, formerly set out as an Economic Stabilization Program note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1904"},"text":"section 1904 of Title 12","children":[],"tail":", Banks and Banking."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 5 of the Emergency Petroleum Allocation Act of 1973, referred to in subsec. (a)(12), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/159/s5"},"text":"section 5 of Pub. L. 93–159","children":[],"tail":", which was classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s754"},"text":"section 754 of Title 15","children":[],"tail":", Commerce and Trade, and was omitted from the Code."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 506(c) of the Natural Gas Policy Act of 1978, referred to in subsec. (a)(13), is classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s3416/c"},"text":"section 3416(c) of Title 15","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 523 of the Energy Policy and Conservation Act, referred to in subsec. (a)(14), is classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s6393"},"text":"section 6393 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id529d8932-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s19/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 19(b)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (1) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (1) read as follows: “of an appeal from a final decision of a district court of the United States, the United States District Court for the District of the Canal Zone, the District Court of Guam, the District Court of the Virgin Islands, or the District Court for the Northern Mariana Islands, if the jurisdiction of that court was based, in whole or in part, on "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1338"},"text":"section 1338 of this title","children":[],"tail":", except that a case involving a claim arising under any Act of Congress relating to copyrights, exclusive rights in mask works, or trademarks and no other claims under section 1338(a) shall be governed by sections 1291, 1292, and 1294 of this title;”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s7/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–29, § 7(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", amended subpar. (A) generally. Prior to amendment, subpar. (A) read as follows: “the Board of Patent Appeals and Interferences of the United States Patent and Trademark Office with respect to patent applications and interferences, at the instance of an applicant for a patent or any party to a patent interference, and any such appeal shall waive the right of such applicant or party to proceed under section 145 or 146 of title 35;”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(10). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s5/g/5/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 5(g)(5)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s7107/a/1"},"text":"section 7107(a)(1) of title 41","children":[],"tail":"” for “section 8(g)(1) of the Contract Disputes Act of 1978 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s607/g/1"},"text":"41 U.S.C. 607(g)(1)","children":[],"tail":")”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s5/g/5/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 5(g)(5)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s7107/b"},"text":"section 7107(b) of title 41","children":[],"tail":"” for “section 10(b) of the Contract Disputes Act of 1978 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s609/b"},"text":"41 U.S.C. 609(b)","children":[],"tail":")”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350/s5/g/5/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350, § 5(g)(5)(C)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s7107/b"},"text":"section 7107(b) of title 41","children":[],"tail":"” for “section 10(b) of the Contract Disputes Act of 1978”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Subsec. (a)(4)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/b/14/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(b)(14)(A)]","children":[],"tail":", inserted “United States” before “Patent and Trademark”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/b/14/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(b)(14)(B)]","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Under Secretary of Commerce for Intellectual Property and Director of the United States Patent and Trademark Office” for “Commissioner of Patents and Trademarks”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(4)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4402/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4402(b)(2)]","children":[],"tail":", substituted “145, 146, or 154(b)” for “145 or 146”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsec. (a)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/572/s902/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–572, § 902(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “United States Court of Federal Claims” for “United States Claims Court”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(11) to (14). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/572/s102/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–572, § 102(c)","children":[],"tail":", added pars. (11) to (14)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/702"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–702","children":[],"tail":" inserted “, exclusive rights in mask works,” after “copyrights”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/418"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–418","children":[],"tail":" substituted “U.S. note 6 to subchapter X of chapter 98 of the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States” for “headnote 6 to schedule 8, part 4, of the Tariff Schedules of the United States”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsec. (a)(4)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/622"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–622","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Patent Appeals and” for “Appeals or the Board of Patent”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id529d8933-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id529d8934-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2011 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s7/c/2"},"text":"section 7(c)(2) of Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":" effective upon the expiration of the 1-year period beginning on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-09-16"},"text":"Sept. 16, 2011","children":[],"tail":", and applicable to proceedings commenced on or after that effective date, with certain exceptions, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s7/e"},"text":"section 7(e) of Pub. L. 112–29","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s6"},"text":"section 6 of Title 35","children":[],"tail":", Patents."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/29/s